com.dlsc.flexgantt.model.scheduling

Class AbstractConstraint<T,S extends IGranularity>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dlsc.flexgantt.model.gantt.DefaultRelationship<T>
      • com.dlsc.flexgantt.model.scheduling.AbstractConstraint<T,S>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the timeline objects
    S - the time granularity
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IRelationship<T>, IConstraint<T,S>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SimpleGranularityConstraint, TimeGranularityConstraint

    public abstract class AbstractConstraint<T,S extends IGranularity>
extends DefaultRelationship<T>
implements IConstraint<T,S>
    An abstract constraint superclass, which can be used by both built-in time granularities SimpleGranularity and TimeGranularity.
    Since:
    2.1
    Author:
    Dirk Lemmermann

    • Method Detail

      • getViolation

        public Violation getViolation(long time1,
                              long time2)
        Description copied from interface: IConstraint
        Checks whether a violation of the constraint exists for the given two time points.
        • If the constraint is of type RelationshipType.END_TO_START then time1will be the end time of the first timeline object and time2 will be the start time of the second timeline object.
        • If the constraint is of type RelationshipType.END_TO_END then time1will be the end time of the first timeline object and time2 will be the end time of the second timeline object.
        • If the constraint is of type RelationshipType.START_TO_START then time1will be the start time of the first timeline object and time2 will be the start time of the second timeline object.
        • If the constraint is of type RelationshipType.START_TO_END then time1will be the start time of the first timeline object and time2 will be the end time of the second timeline object.
        Specified by:
        getViolation in interface IConstraint<T,S extends IGranularity>
        Returns:
        a violation message

      • getDelta

        protected abstract double getDelta(long time1,
                                   long time2,
                                   S granularity)
        Calculates the difference between the two time points for the given granularity. This method needs to be implemented by the subclasses based on the time granularity used by them (e.g. TimeGranularity or SimpleGranularity).
        Parameters:
        time1 - the relevant time point of the first timeline object (might be start or end time)
        time2 - the relevant time point of the second timeline object (might be start or end time)
        granularity - the time granularity (e.g. HOURS, DAYS, ...)
        Returns:
        the delta between the two given time points
        Since:
        2.1
